animal.description: Girly is a beautiful, sweet, cuddly and sensitive Pup. Do you want someone to go on a quick sprint with? Perhaps a detective to go hunting for a treat? Or maybe even a snuggle buddy for Netflix binge watching sessions? Then Girly is your gal! Girly is estimated to be a 5 year old mildly energetic lady who enjoys the thrill of the hunt and outdoors, just as much as she loves curling up on a couch or sunbathing on a patio. Her favorite things to do are car rides and quiet, long walks outdoors. She also seems to be up for a challenge as long as she can explore in a quiet place. This gal has no time for noisy environments! While at home, Girly is one of the calmest and sweetest pups ever. She is house trained and will hide in embarrassment if she has an accident (which is RARE!). She loves being next to her human whether hanging on the couch, belly up sometimes for non-stop rubs before falling asleep with snores that can get quite loud; or, in the kitchen with puppy-dog eyes begging for treats (peanut butter, cheddar cheese and vanilla ice-cream are her favorites!). Girly seemed to have had significant emotional trauma in her past life which makes her very anxious, fearful and a little unsure of herself sometimes. It takes her a long time to warm up to people and other dogs, and she will often have some reactions stemming from her fears, and she would love a patient human who can give her the time and patience to warm up. With continued patient training and a gentle and calming owner, she will blossom into a pleasant doggie who can be around a lot of people and other dogs. This lady is a quiet and mature doggie who is quite content receiving attention from her human rather than chasing after a ball or frisbee. However, she does love a nice run, and doing a good zoomie. She will also hunt for her treats in grass or other toys, and will chew her rope to settle down when she's anxious. Girly's ideal home will be a low-traffic and quiet environment with access to a sizable fenced-yard where she can run around safely at her leisure. Ideally, she would have two humans in the home who can provide her with double the attention she craves. She would also prefer an adult-only home because sometimes kids can be too rambunctious for her. She also would do best as the sole pet in the home. However, she could learn to thrive with another more confident and calmer dog who could give her little peer-to-peer therapy in self-confidence. Come meet this beautiful and cuddly young lady!
animal.name: Girly

animal.description: Are you looking for a silly man to watch those squirrels like a hawk? Then come meet Hawk! Hawk is a chill boy inside, but he would love someone who can help him to understand that his humans will come home eventually. Hawk is someone who bonds very closely with his person and he enjoys affection, but is not too invasive and likes his own space. He is also very smart, and likes to be outside exploring all the things nature has to offer. Hawk is such a polite boy when it comes to going potty. He always waits to go outside and has not had any accidents in the house. Hawk is initially a shy guy, and will take time to get comfortable with you. It's worth the wait though because once he trusts you, he'll enjoy some good belly rubs and pats. He prefers pups who are not overly aggressive and can chill with him, and would need a well-matched dog buddy. Hawk is super easy to walk on leash, but he is still learning not to pull. He loves to sniff and explore a lot, but is also responsive to any command to move along. What he really absolutely adores is watching those action filled squirrels. If you even say the word squirrel, he'll get super attentive and look around to find those silly squirrels. He loves being outside and exploring and sniffing everything. If you have a yard where he can chase squirrels, he would be over the moon. Nothing drives him crazier than a squirrel in sight! He will chase them like crazy. Hawk never jumps on the bed or sofa and knows that's not his space. He would thrive in a low-traffic and calm home with a yard where he can run and chase those squirrels he loves. He would also be okay in an apartment without stairs or hallways. Come meet this sweet boy!

animal.description: Beryl is a boy who can do it all! Not only is he full of spunk and personality, but he'll also make you laugh, shower you with love and impress you with all his skills. Although Beryl can be shy with new friends, he'll shamelessly beg for belly rubs and butt scritches when he's had time to warm up. Despite his 'senior' status, he has plenty of energy for long walks, outdoor adventures and two-toy fetch. And did we mention that Beryl's an excellent houseguest? He's house-trained, crate-trained and happy to snooze when you're gone! Because he loves to soak up all the spotlight, Beryl would prefer to be the only pet in the home (though he'd be willing to make an exception for the perfect furry friend!). He's not up for house parties, so he does best in a chill, adult-only environment. Beryl comes with a ton of skills and is a highly trained dog. He's an APA! TOP (Total Obedience Program) Ready dog who receives one-on-one sessions with a volunteer trainer each week. Beryl is a master at both basic and advanced obedience, and even knows to go to his special 'place' when someone knocks on the door. As part of APA!'s TOP Dog program, you can work with our staff to continue Beryl's training post-adoption, helping you master all of his tricks together! Learn more about TOP here: https://vimeo.com/89434193 Follow along with Beryl's adventures on Instagram @goodestboyberyl!

animal.description: JJ Watt is a gorgeous young pup who is just as smart and fun as he is good-looking! He takes a little time to warm up to new friends, but once you earn his trust, he is a sweet and goofy boy. He'll keep you smiling with his cute little hops when he's excited to see you and when he is about to go for a walk. He also has a great enthusiasm for snacks! While JJ enjoys attention from his best human friends, he isn't overly-clingy. He does like his space at times (but don't we all), and he'll let you know you're his person with some gentle head nuzzles on your arm. He will also hang out near you while you're relaxing or getting some work done. He's a big fan of going on easy-paced strolls to get his exercise, and will take plenty of opportunities to stop and smell all the things. He also loves to plop down on a good patch of grass and roll around to scratch his back! JJ Watt has been enjoying learning new things, and is in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, JJ Watt has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! As a part of APA's Total Obedience Program, you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with JJ Watt after adoption, and master all of the TOP dog skills together! Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https://vimeo.com/89434193 JJ Watt would love a low-traffic home with one or two adults to call his own. If you're looking for a handsome, sweet and easy-to-please dog to add to your life, come meet JJ Watt - he's truly a special soul!

animal.description: This pup has the scoop on being your new best friend! While he may be shy at first, Scoopy quickly warms up to anyone, and he'll only leave your side to snag the comfy spot on the couch. This good boy has had a tough time in the world but you wouldn't know it by his gentle, sweet demeanor! He is working on being more confident, so he is looking for a loving and patient family to help guide him through the scary sounds of the outside world ('Sirens! Beeping! Engines! Oh my!). Once he is comfortable in new situations, he is the happiest, energetic pup. He'll even show you his athletic side if you have a ball to throw! Scoopy could qualify for the Olympic High Jump team, so he would do best in a (high!) fenced backyard where he can run around safely. Inside the house, Scoopy loves to cuddle up and binge a good show. He will snuggle up into ANY space you allow him to, even your lap! Don't let his size fool you! He is the perfect work-from-home officemate, and will even remind you to take frequent yoga breaks with his downward dog stretches. He is a quick learner and has got 'sit down pretty well if there's a yummy treat involved. Scoopy is house-trained, and will let you know when he needs to go outside by hanging out by the door. If you let him, Scoopy will gladly hop on to any bed you give him, but he is also used to being in his crate at night for sleeping. Scoopy loves playdates with furry friends, and could do well in a home with other dogs. Scoopy is Heartworm positive, but all that means is that he will need a few months rest after treatment at APA!'s expense, and then he will be better than ever. He will need a home that will make sure he makes it to his appointments at APA!, and will give him extra love as he goes through the treatment process. Scoopy's most favorite thing is cuddling and nestling his face and big floppy ears on your lap. Do you have a spot for him at your home? Don't let this good boy get passed up, come meet him today!
animal.name: Scoopy

animal.description:
Hello world, meet Piper! Piper is a sweet mixed breed who is looking for her forever home. She loves to chase balls, play tug of war, and roll over for some belly rubs. Piper has so much energy that she will need a home with a fenced back yard with plenty of room to work off that energy. Because of her larger than life personality, she is not aware of her own size and could knock over small children so we suggest a home with older kiddos. Piper is also good with other dogs! She is potty trained and kenneled trained as well. Her adoption fee is $150.00 and includes spaying, rabies, vaccinations, and microchipping. If you are interested in meeting her, apply at www.ootwrescue.org.

To make the best possible match for you and the pet, please click below to complete the Adoption Application. 

Once your application has been processed, we'll be in contact. 

We cannot schedule a meet and greet without a completed application. 

If you are viewing this page through PetFinder, Adopt-a-Pet, etc., please go to http://ootwrescue.org/adoption.html to fill out an application or review our Adoption Process.

As with all our dogs, Apollo must be an indoor dog.
If you are interested in adopting Apollo, please email bahshelter@yahoo.com. If there are other dogs in your home, we require a meet and greet, which you can schedule via email at bahshelter@yahoo.com. 
If you cannot attend your scheduled visit, kindly text or call the volunteer you are meeting before your scheduled visit. They are taking time out of their day to meet with you. Thank you!

animal.description:
Meet Bert!

Bert was surrendered to the San Diego Humane Society-Oceanside

his family who could no longer care for him.

He is 8 years old and weighs 17 lbs. On January 6th, Bert became a Frosted Face!

He has a heart murmur, a collapsing trachea, and some arthritis in his right elbow, but Bert doesn't let any of that slow him down! We use a harness to walk him to relieve pressure on his neck. Bert is a fun guy who asks for belly rubs and pets!

Bert was only at Frosted Faces a few days before he got to go to a Foster home to wait for his Forever Family. His Foster Family shared this update:

"Bert is a super fun dog who loves scratches, cuddling, and his blanket! He's potty trained, great on a leash, loves to cuddle, and pretty much ignores other dogs that he has met although he and our dog are starting to have some playful interactions. We have had him in a crate at night but may let him have more freedom since he's doing so well. He has a very healthy appetite and is always ready to pounce on any food left unattended. His favorite place seems to be next to my teenager!"

Be sure to watch the adorable videos of Bert with his favorite blankie and his tail wagging a mile a minute! There's also a video of Bert on a walk with this Foster Family.

If you'd like to meet Bert, apply here: https://frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Apply to become a family: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated 1/31/21 KG

animal.description:
Dasher was adopted but returned a week later due to adopter's dog being to excited to play with a new dog buddy. Dasher was perfect at their home and very welll behaved. They decided they are not ready for 2 dogs.
Dasher's time was up at the shelter since he was nervous of the shelter food test with fake hand on pole. We evaluated him with treats/chews and had no issues by hand and took him in. He did great with our transporter and well behaved during his car ride. Very nice dog. Dasher needs basic training. Fine on leash. He is very friendly happy listens and is cooperative. He is very treat motivated and smart. Dasher loves playing with other dogs. He is doing great at his hero foster home and their GSD dog. They are already playing on day one. Dasher needs to time to heal from his neuter surgery. Dasher is a sweetie. He will need an experienced guardian and home with attached backyard. Due to his size he will need dog experienced kids and 14 yrs and up. Dasher would be happiest with another dog at home if possible. More info. to come from his foster home.
Update 1/30/21: Dasher is super sweet and loving. He has gotten along with all humans and dogs he has met. He loves to run around and play with other dogs. He loves getting his belly rubbed and will cuddle up with you on the couch. He also loves being outside playing in the yard with toys or sunbathing on our deck. He is treat motivated. Has learned sit down and paw. He can still get a little bit mouthy when he is excited but responds well when you tell him 'no'. He does not like being crated but sleeps through the night on his dog bed in our room with us. He knows his voice and can be vocal. He will bark when trying to engage a dog to play with him at the park or when inside and someone is walking past on the sidewalk but doesn't bark while walking on a leash. No signs of aggression always backs down if a dog snaps at him. Takes treats easily and will let you take things out of his mouth. Will let you brush his teeth and clip his toe nails.YouTube: https://youtu.be/pz3hGnTq6_Y

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET PLEASE SUBMIT THE ADOPTION APPLICATION VIA OUR WEBSITE: WWW.TAILSOFHOPEDOGRESCUE.COM. THANK YOU! ADOPTION IS $150.00.

Darcie is a doll! This puppy is all fun and games! She was born about 11/2/20, is current on all vaccinations, has been wormed, is current on heartworm and flea prevention, and has been microchipped. She is great with other dogs, wonderful with children and seems fine with cats. Our best guess is she is a small lab mix. She weighed in at ten pounds Jan 3. of this year.  She absolutely needs a home with a fenced yard and another dog. She loves running and playing so much outside with her doggie friends. She is smart, has a sweet disposition and would make a great family addition.  Darcie is in Memphis.
She will be  spayed at approx. 14 weeks of age. She is located in Memphis. We do permit local approved applicants to enter into our foster-to-adopt program with puppies waiting to be spayed/neutered as they cannot be adopted until such time.

animal.description:
Champ is being fostered in PA

What Champ's foster mom has to say about Champ:
Champ has really come out of his shell over the last few months! He came to us in October and has been undergoing treatment for HeartWorm and on cage rest. Since he's finished that up, his reserve is evaporating, and he has begun seeking out attention and learning to enjoy life again! Champ is very easy going and laid back. He loves food and was easily house trained here after a little bit of work. Champ enjoys napping on couches, chairs, dog begs, people beds, or anything comfy. Napping is his hobby! He walks pretty well on a leash. We use an easy walk harness for extra control and guidance. Champ is a big boy and a bit clumsy at times, but he's a super sweet guy who will steal your heart along with your snack if you're not looking! He gets along well with our teenage kids and our other large dogs. We don't have young children, small dogs, or cats, but he would probably be okay with them as long as they are respectful of him. He's a live and let live kind of dog. He is blind
BDRA has voted against the use of electrical fencing effective immediately.

animal.description:
Meet sweet Daniel, he was living near a church along with his homeless owner but was abandoned by his owner for unknown reasons. The members of the church were Daniel was abandoned helped this cutie and are now wanting to find him a loving home. Daniel is a neutered male Pitbull terrier mix (he has been DNA tested – American PBT 61%, AmStaff 19.2%, Australian Cattle Dog 10.1%, Chinese Shar-Pei 9.7%)

This cutie is about 67 pounds and pretty healthy. Daniel does have seasonal allergies but can easily be treated. This cutie loves humans and he does well with dogs his size or even larger than him. Daniel has not been around cats so we have no idea how he will do in a home with a cat. Daniel is pretty energetic so he will do best with an active family since he loves playing outside. This boy is also potty trained and crate trained so he is a pretty good boy. 

You can view video of Daniel at https://fb.watch/35Mfe07FvC/


If interested in Daniel please visit our website www.bravebullyrescue.org and fill out our adoption application. 


If you will like to get more information on Daniel please email Abby at abby.bassett@sanofi.com

animal.description:
Trevor von Traben is a striking, larger-sized 2 year-old sable German Shepherd. This hunky young man is looking for a compassionate leader to guide him down the path of success. Trevor bounces with happiness when one of his favorite people appears at his kennel door to take him out for a walk. His tendency to pull ahead with excitement is quickly checked with a minor correction. One would think that a dog of Trevor's size and stature would be brave and bold, but this fledgling to the urban environment needs an experienced handler who can show him how to feel safe and comfortable. Once he feels at ease, this sweet and affectionate boy will melt with pleasure, especially if a head rub is involved! In playgroups, Trevor is still too shy to engage with the other dogs and will object to pushy dogs approaching him. This strapping head-turner will thrive in a loving home where he will be given the time to reach his potential and blossom.

animal.description: WILLOW came to us from a backyard breeding situation. A former volunteer of ours saw her posted on craigslist for free. She was originally owned by someone and given to her neighbor after her previous owner moved out and left her behind. Not knowing she wasnt spayed, the new owners housed her with an unaltered male and she became pregnant. After selling her puppies, the new owners now decided to rehome her due to some skin issues that they could not afford to take care of. ((was all told to us, we do not know WILLOWs true story)) but from the looks of her when she came to us she was definitely a backyard dog and not very well taken care of. Her body has several scars, she came to us with a massive bacterial skin infection. One of her ears looks like they attempted to crop her and failed. Her personality is a little goofy and and she can be a bit ditsy. But Willow is a sweetheart. She would absolutely love a home where she can spend the rest of her days snuggling. She loves humans. Shes a leaner. She can be a little shy but again an expert cuddler.

animal.description:
Hi my name is Sarge, I am a 2 year old Anatolian shepherd and great Pyrenees mix. I am the BEST boy! That is, of course, assuming there aren't any scary things out there... I am potty trained and I'm a good boy at night out of the crate. That crate scares me! I am extra sure to be good so I don't have to go in there. I LOVE other dogs and even cats. I like to play with stuffed toys, and ropes are my absolute favorite!!! Foster mom says I just tear apart the stuffed ones but I think that's what they are for. Why else would they be so fun to destroy??

Foster mom says I would do best in a home with kids over 10... the little ones move really quick, and can be really scary... I don't really like men either, they have been pretty scary in the past too. I listen very well! If you call for me I will come, just not too loud, please... I still get a little scared with loud yells. I just flatten out like a pancake on the ground and wait for foster mom to tell me what to do.

I am great on a leash with my harness and I can even go outside without a leash to go to the fence and back inside the house because foster mom gives me a treat and I really like that! My favorite treat is ice cubes, they come right out of foster moms fridge.

I have had a rough year and I am looking for a special family to enjoy my snuggles. I am protective of my house and really don't like strangers. They are something else I'm afraid of... I am scared of what they will do, so I keep my distance and sometimes growl to tell them I am scared if they get to be too much for me. Foster mom tells people this when they come to the house and she always hugs them to help me understand they are good people, this helps me smell them a little.

I love my foster moms kids, they are very aware that I get nervous with fast movement and loud noises. Foster mom says I will find my people that will help me be less afraid, and I will keep feeling more secure as time passes.

animal.description:
Meet Merry. 
Merry is a sweet 2 ish year old pittie mix girl. Found as a stray and very pregnant this girl was welcomed to the placing paws family to be given a safe haven to have and raise her pups but also to ensure her a better “happy ending”. We know she has had a home because she knows sit and shake, is good in the crate and car and appears potty trained. She Love love loves toys!! She loves to fetch. And she loves to just lay by her person. She takes about 2 minutes And 2 treats to warm up to men but has been great around kids  8 and up ( we just haven’t seen her around little kids yet)  She prefers to be the only dog. Merry is as deserving as they come. Could you give her the happy ever after she so deserves!!! 

ADOPTION FEE: $350.00 The adoption fee includes all age appropriate vaccinations including rabies, HW test if age appropriate, de-worming, microchip, fecal, spay or neuter, Heartworm and flea and tick preventative.  ADOPTION PROCESS: PLEASE READ CAREFULLY The first step in the adoption process is to fill out an application online at www.placingpawsrescue.org. Once we review the applications, those applicants that are thought to be a good match will be contacted as quickly as possible. We ask that you please be patient with us as we are all volunteers. Then a telephone interview will take place, references checked and a home visit will be conducted. We will then arrange for you to meet the dog. We require that all family members, including current dogs meet the dog prior to adoption.  We put all of the known information in the animals description. If the animal is listed on the website, we are still accepting applications for that animal. We only remove the animal when the final adoption paperwork is signed. The best way to contact us is by email at placingpaws@yahoo.com. It is very difficult for the limited numbers of volunteers to return all calls. Thank you.

animal.description:
Foster – Husky mix – 1yr. – male (70 lbs.)

Meet our big goofy boy, Foster! Foster was surrendered to a county shelter because his owners said he was too active for them. He is active, but the real problem is that he wasn’t properly trained when he was little and now he’s being blamed for being a big puppy with no manners. We’ve found that while Foster does need to learn manners, he is also smart and willing to learn if given a chance and some time. Foster truly is a big, happy puppy who thinks everything is a game. He has a lot of energy and will need a person or family that is active and busy and will include him in their activities. We believe he’s housebroken because he rarely has accidents in his kennel area. Foster loves to play with other dogs, but with his size and energy level, he can be a bit much for some dogs. He does best with active dogs that like rough play. Foster also loves kids, but would probably knock over little ones, so a home with older kids or teens would be a great fit. He would also be great with a runner – he can definitely keep up. Our sweet boy is nothing but love and is looking for someone to give all his love to. He wants someone to love and care for him and, in return, he will provide years of loyal commitment and unconditional love – who could ask for anything more. To get the chance to meet our silly boy, Foster, please fill out an application to start the process.

Hi everyone! Meet Alvin (aka Taysom by his current foster family who are huge Saints fans) He is a fun- loving black mouth cur/ lab mix. He was born around October 21st and weighs about 13 pounds. He will be medium to large when full grown. He is working on potty and kennel training, but much rathers being cuddled in the bed. Alvin loves to play, especially with toys that make noise and is great with kids. He also loves playing along with other dogs! Although he hasnt spent too much time with cats, we believe he would be just fine with a feline friend. Overall, he is such a sweet pup that deserves a great forever home! He is UTD on shots.

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee their breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information.

Puppies under 12 months - $300

Hello Friends, I'm KEENA. I am a 5/6 year old shepherd mix. I do need to lose some weight to be healthy, but I'm working on it! I do love to go on walks, and everyone says I have good manners on walks. Thinks like noisy trucks and people on bicycles do not seem to bother me. My coat is full of many shades of white, tan, gray, brown and black, and I have no tail! I promise to take treats gently and let you pet me as long as you want; belly rubs are my favorite! I never bark and as much as I love walks, I also love to relax by your feet. I am housebroken and know basic commands. I am gentle with the household cat and children. Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee.
 
All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.
 
Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab at JRsPupsNStuff.org. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.

I'd love for everyone to meet Mary! Mary is Momma to the Elf litter, and all of her babies were adopted at the end of last year.....now it's Mary's turn!??

Mary is a (approximately) 50 pound, 4 year old "mixed breed" -- which just means she is a true mutt. Mary had a rough beginning to life from what we can tell, but she is SO forgiving and truly focused on her humans. 

Mary is a mouthy dog, she nips and nibbles when she wants to be pet or wants attention -- she has never shown an aggressiveness in doing this, but due to this, Mary needs to be in a home with no children. 

Mary is also a high energy dog, while many of the photos I have of her are of her sleeping, she has recently found entertainment in toys! Frequently, in the mornings (or really after any nap), Mary will run and toss toys to herself -- she does create a little bit of a ruckus, but she is SO cute!

animal.description:
Meet Dylan! Dylan is around 1 year old and 40lbs. Great with dogs of all ages, housetrained, and good with kids. He had a leg injury and was in a splint for a while. It has healed with some extra calcification that makes him limp a little (especially first thing in the morning or after he’s been in his crate) but otherwise doesn’t seem to bother him.
 Dylan is a cuddly, easy-going, loveable guy who thinks snow is his personal reward for being such a good boy. He may get a little nervous meeting new people, but gets attached quickly and loves to play and snuggle. 
 His old leg injury doesn’t slow him down at all in his quest to get out, explore, and smell the big exciting world. 

Interested in this sweet dog? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

**Please note: Our animals live in foster homes throughout the Madison area. We do not have a shelter where animals are available for daily viewing. Applying is the first step in our process.**

Dogs from Underdog Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
Spay/Neuter
Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella Vaccinations (as age appropriate-puppy adopters may need to cover some vaccine boosters)
Heartworm Test (for dogs over 6mo)
Microchip
Deworming
Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

Our adult dog adoption fee is $300. Our puppy (under 5 mo) is $375. Our senior dog (over 8 yrs) is $250.

*Please note that all breeds noted are estimates or best guesses. We very rarely have information on our animals' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays*

animal.description:
Please DO NOT APPLY OR INQUIRE IF:

1) You live in a high traffic area
2) you have children
3) you have large dogs 
4) your cat is not dog savvy 
5) you live outside the lower mainland 

We will not respond to general inquiries through petfinder platform, please submit the adoption application AFTER reading his full profile.

Please go to our website and submit the online adoption application by copying and pasting this link into your browser

www.lowermainlandhumanesociety.org/adoption-application/


Finch is about 7 years old.  He's a chihuahua but might have a little Jack Russell terrier in him, which makes him a little more tenacious than a typical chihuahua.

Finch is best with dogs his size or maybe just slightly larger, and better with Females.  He is a bit competitive with other male dogs.  He is not fond of large dogs so please don't make him live with one. 

He does get along with the resident cats but sometimes he aggressively chases them. 

Finch does not like to kiss on the first or second dates so please don't stick your face in his face, unless you want a free nose piercing. 

Finch would not be suitable for a home with children or frequent visiting children. 

He has bilateral luxating patellas that occasionally pop in and out.  But he walks just fine 90% of the time 

If you have high furniture or a high bed you must have dog stairs for him to get off without jumping and potentially injuring himself. 

Finch is very scared of cars and should absolutely not live in high traffic areas.  This would be an accident waiting to happen if he were to get spooked and get away from his human.  

Finch is not a candidate for off leash dog parks or off leash walking.  

He is very affectionate and loving.  He absolutely loves his human and is a good listener.  He would prefer to have his own yard that is fenced, even if it is a small yard.  He loves to sleep under the covers.  And he walks well on leash in quiet areas. He's on a special diet that is Royal Canin Hypoallergenic because he does have some food allergies but it's nothing serious. 

Finch is a sweetheart and just loves to cuddle with his person, sit on the sofa and watch TV and cuddle in bed at night. 

His adoption fee is 495$
He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, flea treated, dewormed and has an upcoming dental in February. 

An adoption application and home visit is required. 

Please go to our website and submit the online adoption application by copying and pasting this link into your browser

www.lowermainlandhumanesociety.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Say hello to Cozy—Cozy is 10 years old, weighs in at 10 pounds and we believe she is a mini poodle.  

Cozy does have the senior trifecta (no teeth, mostly blind and mostly deaf) but this does not stop her from living her best life!!!!  She is a well-mannered, sweet and laid back girl who want nothing more than to live the retirement life. 

Below is a quick list of more information on Cozy:

•	Housebroken 
•	Crate trained
•	Great with kids of all ages
•	Good with dogs
•	Good with cats
•	Travels great in vehicles
•	Diet- requires soft food
•	Personality:  She can be timid and shy at first but as she has settled into her foster home she has become more confident
•	Cuteness factor: Since she has no teeth her tongue hangs out the left side of her mouth in the most adorable way 

Cozy is amazing and would love nothing more than to cuddle on the couch with her special human or to hit the road as the best travel companion ever!!!

If you think Cozy may be the one for you, please go to our website at www.wagstorichesanimalrescue.org and fill out an application to adopt. Please be sure to include a vet reference as regular vet care is important to us for the health of all our adopted dogs. With approval and a $150 Golden Paws adoption donation, she will be ready to accompany you on all of life’s many adventures!  Cozy is spayed, microchipped, fecal tested clean of internal parasites and up to date on all her vaccinations, including rabies.

animal.description:
Big boy, big head, big heart! Handsome Sarge is big in all ways! Sarge is a 5 1/2 year old bully breed mix with a heart of gold! Sarge originally came to CCR from a rural animal control facility in southern Illinois where he had been found stray. He was adopted but sadly returned several months later when his adopter found that the highrise-apartment-lifestyle was not what was best for Sarge. It's clear from Sarge's behavior that he is used to be an outside dog - he's independent, smart, confident, and friendly. He acts just like a dog who was used to making his own decisions about how he'd spend his days. Moving into the confines and structure of a super urban downtown lifestyle caused Sarge too much stress - he needs a home with some space to stretch his legs, smell the flowers, and enjoy his time outdoors before coming inside for a good snooze and snuggle sesh! Sarge would do well with a home that has a fenced yard and a family that lives a more suburban or rural lifestyle - Sarge is a country boy at heart! He'll do best as an only dog, but he'll bring so much joy that you won't miss having a second pet! Because Sarge does have a strong personality, he's best suited for homes that have previous dog experience. He's a bit too much dog for first-time pet owners.

To meet Sarge, please submit an application at chicagocaninerescue.org!

animal.description:
A SWEET GIVER OF KISSES:  5 years old / 41 lbs.

Hello there!  My name is Charmaigne!  I’m a sweetie who came to Mostly Mutts from animal control in need of cherry eye surgery, and with infected ears making me quite uncomfortable.  Mostly Mutts has treated my ears and I’ve had my cherry eye surgery, so I’m feeling much better and looking great too!

• OTHER DOGS/CATS/KIDS:  No dogs please as I react negatively to other dogs in an aggressive way / Cat’s unknown / I met a 10-year-old boy and his younger sister at Mostly Mutts and did well with them, so a home with kid friends around that age (10 or slightly younger) could be fun, let’s meet!  But please don’t let kids walk me due to my dislike of other dogs.  

• PERSONALITY/ENERGY LEVEL:  I am a happy girl who is a shelter favorite – friendly with all the people I have met.  My sweet, affectionate nature has me resting my head on you and giving you loving kisses. My former foster mom says I was an excellent house guest and companion. I was very calm in the house, and I followed her around and laid by her side while she worked. / My energy level is 3-5.

• SKILLS/CRATE/POTTY:  I am a student in the Mostly Mutts University training program, where I have already mastered the ‘sit’, ‘stay’, ‘come’, ‘down’, and ‘leave it’ commands as well as proper door etiquette and accepting nice strangers without jumping. I walk well on the leash without a lot of distractions. I bet you can teach me even more / My crate manners are good at Mostly Mutts and in my former foster home (I barked a bit if I could hear my foster family in the house). / I’ve had very good potty habits on the shelter schedule and in my former foster home.  

• LIKES/DISLIKES:  I like spending time with the volunteers who care for me.  I load nicely into the car, so maybe I can accompany you to some fun places where we can spend time together / I don’t like other dogs (see above), and the horses at my former foster home scared me. I also would not be happy if I did not get the love, training and attention all doggies deserve! 

• MEDICAL:  I'm current on vaccinations, micro-chipped and spayed. I had surgery in early January to correct cherry eye in both eyes, and I will need an additional surgery. Mostly Mutts will cover the cost. 

I am looking for a loving home where I will be a cherished family member!  My adoption fee is $299.00, and I’m located in Kennesaw, Ga.

animal.description: Let me introduce myself, my name is Bear. I weigh in at about 20lbs, not too big, not too small... and I'm about 7 years old. The folks here at Green Dog Rescue Project took me out of the local shelter in June of 2015, and I eventually found a great home with a wonderful older gentleman. I lived happily with my guy for the past 4.5 years, then my world turned upside down again. My guy became ill... and eventually he passed away. It was hard losing him, and I felt so lost and uncertain as to my future. His adult children arrived at the home, everyone was so upset. They didn't seem to understand what my routine and schedule was, and I didn't understand why they were packing up all of the things that belonged to my guy. Things that made me feel comfortable and safe. Eventually, the people looked at me and asked "What are we going to do with you?" Apparently no one was willing or able to take me in, and because I was feeling more and more nervous and uncertain, I began to act out. I understood they were as upset about losing their dad as I was, but I don't think they understood that "I" was upset and confused too. Well, it didn't take long for things to go south... I felt their distress and confusion, and at some point I lost my patience and snapped at one of the ladies trying to grab me. She just moved a little too fast and scared me, I know it was wrong, but I didn't know what else to do. I just reacted. I didn't really hurt her, I was just trying to warn her to slow down and take some time to let me adjust to all these changes. Well, that was the day they returned me to Green Dog Rescue Project. The folks here have given me some time to adjust back into a life I'm familiar with. And I'm ready now to find another home to share with a human. I like other dogs, prefer older men, am not overly anxious to meet new people, and find that I like a simple routine in my life. Perhaps a retired man like the one I had before, with a quiet household and daily walks would be best suited for me. I'm not very comfortable with a lot of company and excitement going on in my home, so an easygoing lifestyle would be most appealing to me. Once we get to know each other, I absolutely LOVE to be with you... your little shadow. Initially, I'm a pain in the behind (just being honest here)... and I don't interview very well... but that is mostly because I'm a bit of an introvert and don't know if I should trust people. If you can give me a few minutes to explore who YOU are before you reach out to grab or pet me, then after that I can be very affectionate, loyal, and a cuddler once I settle in and understand the routine. We just need a little time to get to know one another. If you would like to get to know me, perhaps you could come by for a visit, maybe take me out for a couple of walks, and then take me home for a week long trial.... I'd love to get to know you better too.

animal.description:
Deacon is a sweet cattle dog/border collie mix. He is 15 weeks old and loves to play with his foster siblings. Deacon’s rescue journey started out rough… He was found with a deep laceration to his back leg and had to undergo surgery. The drain tube was removed right after Christmas and he is healing beautifully! Deacon is great with toddlers, other dogs, and cats. We are still learning that the cat doesn’t like to play! Deacon is very good with going potty outside and is fully crate trained. He loves playing in the snow and running around outside! Deacon loves to cuddle and thinks he is a lap dog, so we are working on boundaries since he still has a lot of growing to do… But it’s hard to resist his sweet puppy snuggles! Deacon can’t wait to meet his forever family!"

Please email us directly for a faster response and we will send you our questionnaire.   info@petsandpeople.com   We get many each day so please watch your spam/trash folders for our replies.

Adoption fee for all dogs and puppies is $130.00 each, which includes spay/neuter, vaccinations (including all puppy boosters for puppies under 4 months), worming, flea/tick treatment if needed, microchip and collar/leash/tags.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Lacey is an adorable Pit mix that was born on or around 6/1/2016. Lacey has a story that is best shared by her foster mom.

Meet Lacey.

Weight: About 70 lbs. (

She could stand to lose a few pounds but who's counting? )

Health: HW negative & on preventative. Spayed. Up to date on shots. Some scars.

Age: About 4 or 5 years old.

Housebroken.

Crate trained.

Leash trained but hasn't had much exposure to other humans or animals while on leash.

Knows sit, wait, off, & "Go to your room [crate]."

No cats.

She hasn't been around small children.

Takes treats gently from your hand.

Personality: She's a princess and could be an only dog, but plays well with boy dogs.

Happy but easily overexcited & sometimes jealous of other dogs when they receive attention.

She will guard her food or treats from other dogs but shares toys well.

She loves shredding stuffed animals!

She's a very content girl. She's definitely an indoor girl, especially if there's even a hint of rain.

Loves to snuggle on the couch but looks forward to her nightly romp around the backyard chasing a semi-deflated basketball.

Prefers sleeping in the bed with humans but does just fine in the crate.

She was literally dumped at our house last January - thin, hungry, terrified and had lots of wounds. She's smart. She figured out how to survive and then how to trust. It took some time & a lot of work, but she has turned into a sweet, loving dog.

She has been around lots of teenagers but rowdiness upsets her.

She needs someone who will continue to work with her to overcome stranger anxiety.

More than anything she needs to find her Person. More than anything she wants to belong to someone.

Amazing Grace Bully Rescue is a foster based rescue in the Pensacola, Florida area. We do not have a physical building. If you would like to meet any of our pups, the first step is to fill out our online application so we can contact you.

Our adoption fee for Lacey is $200 and includes her spay, current shots,, rabies vaccine, and a registered microchip.

If you would like to adopt this Amazing dog, please fill out our online adoption application at www.amazinggracebullyrescue.org

If you have any questions, please text your question to 723-2037. You may also send a message to our Amazing Grace Bully Rescue Page on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, or send an email directly to amazinggracebullyrescue@gmail.com

Disclaimer: We are located in the Pensacola, Florida area and will consider local applicants first, especially with puppies since we use a vet in the local area.

animal.breeds_label: American Staffordshire Terrier & Black Mouth Cur Mix
animal.description:
Hi,  My name is WALLY.  What's yours?  It's nice to meet you.  WATCH MY VIDEO: https://youtu.be/63DzjXB6vaQ

I was hit by a car and left for dead until a Good Samaritan picked me up out of the street and saved my life.  Then, my life got a WHOLE lot better when a rescue took me in and had the surgery done on my leg that I needed so I could walk again.  I am ALL healed up and ready to go to my new home with YOU!  Yes, I have a scar.  Yes, I walk a little funny, but not too much.  Yes, I have to be somewhat careful but, basically, I am ready to rock n' roll. Maybe you have a little something wrong, too, but I promise I will still love you!

The rescue wants me to have a fenced in yard and they tell me that you need to have an excellent vet history for a current or previous dog.  OK?

I am a Staffy/Black Mouth Cur mix.  (Did you know that Pit/Staffys were used as babysitters during World War II?  If the lady of the house was outside hanging laundry, for instance,  and the children needed her, we would notify the mom that the kids needed her.  Pretty cool, huh?)  I am 1 and 1/2 years old and I weigh 50 pounds. I have been neutered and am up to date on vaccines so I'm ready to go to my new home with YOU!!  Those funny-looking 2-legged creatures said I’m also microchipped – whatever THAT is.  At any rate, I am fully vetted.  Is that anything close to petted?  I love to be petted!  They say I'm precious.  Hmmm, Is my name Wally or Precious?

Wanna hear some more good stuff about me?  OK, here goes.  I like ALL people and ALL dogs.  I am especially good with dogs smaller than I am.  They love me and I love them.  I need to have a smaller DOGGIE SIBLING so we can romp together and burn up lots of energy!   I know basic commands.  I respond very well to consistent, positive reinforcement training and I'm a good learner!  Smart, huh?

I am attentive, affectionate, silly, playful and loyal.  I LOVE cuddles, car rides, and tummy rubs.  I'm an amazing companion!  I still have lots to learn.  I DO know how to use a doggie door. YAY ME!!!  Will you teach me all the things a young rescue dog needs to know to be safe and happy? I LOVE to give kisses so get ready!  

If you have children, then need to be older children - 12 and up because the rescue doesn't want little kids pulling my tail or squeezing me too tightly or, accidentally, letting me out of a door or gate. 

I like to take naps when I'm tired from playing.  I need  love, exercise and couch-sitting when we get tired!  Let's be a team, OK?

If you would like to take me home (and you know you do), please email rescuedogsgalore@gmail.com and they can get me on my way to a new and loving home!  Once you adopt me, I will be flown to Seattle from Houston, TX.  (Seattle is the only place we can fly to right now.)  My adoption fee is $450 and includes my vetting, neutering, flight cost, travel crate, Health Certificate and a microchip.

animal.description:
Franklin is a senior dog (the vet estimated between 10-11 years) that has not had an easy life up until now—but he is currently learning about the little joys in life, including zoomies, full/regular meals, in-between snacks, and soft beds and blankets (where he spends most of his day sleeping). 

Franklin is mostly blind and deaf so the way to communicate with him is touch, however, he is not fond of being touched or picked up by strangers. He needs a patient and kind adopter that is willing to give him the time that he needs to feel comfortable. Franklin generally is not used to human affection and will not seek it out on his own. He is slowly learning that he does like certain things like ear rubs though (once he is comfortable with you). 

Franklin needs a home where no children live or frequently visit. He would do best in a quiet home with other calm, good-natured pets and where someone is home most of the time. He needs frequent potty breaks and will use the bathroom outside every time he is taken out. He will have accidents if he does not get outside frequently enough. It is also important that any stairs in the home can be blocked off so that Franklin does not accidently fall.

We are on the hunt for the perfect retirement home for Franklin where he can continue to thrive and grow.

**Please note we only do adoptions within 2 hours of Atlanta, GA**
Approximate age: 10-11 years
Approximate weight: 9 pounds (currently gaining, should be at least 12)

animal.description: Icarus came to PACC with his friend Sky who has since gone to foster, leaving Icarus all alone. Icarus and Sky lived with the same family their whole lives, but the pandemic took its toll and they were forced to surrender their beloved dogs. Icarus has lived with kids as young as five and his family told us that he's very loving and likes to go for walks. In play group, Icarus greeted other dogs with a waggy tail and had a blast playing in the water and laying down in the pools. He was social and tolerant with other dogs, but we still recommend a meet and greet with any resident dogs. Volunteers say Icarus is a gentle and sweet dog and we just know he'd love to get out of the shelter and into a home. If you want to meet Icarus, make an appointment today.

I am about 3 years old and 30lbs. I'm learning to be more independent, but sometimes get anxious when I'm alone. I am incredibly active - I love walks, playing tug, and chasing the ball. New humans can also make me nervous but, with time, I will cuddle up with anyone. I'm looking for a patient, caring, and active individual to share my days with, take me on adventures, and love me for forever." She has not spent time around children, so older or no children at this time.

animal.description:
CHLOE – 7 Year Old Black Female Lab   70 lbs     Spayed
 
Background:
Chloe was surrendered to the Ukiah shelter as her current owners did not have time for her with their third child on the way and she was currently not doing well with the small dogs in the home. Her story over the last 5 years goes like this: She was purchased from a breeder in the Gridley area and they had her two years, but they felt like they could not keep up with a young active Lab. They took her to the Gridley shelter, and she was rescued for the current owner’s grandson. They had the dog for 2 years and they ended up getting a divorce. (When Chloe was in the home, they had no issues with Chloe.) Chloe then went to the Ex-Daughter in law who kept her for 1 year but had to give her up as Chloe kept getting out of the yard; she had low fences. (She did not have any issues with Chloe other than getting out of the yard.) She then went to the daughter who had her for 2 years. Chloe did great in the home and would sit by her feet while she worked from home. She was a big part of the family but the last 6 months she started to have some issues. They had two small dogs in the home and Chloe would pick them up and shake them. She also ended up catching one of the chickens and killing the chicken. She was around other larger dogs with this family and did not have any issues. Chloe was not getting regular exercise with this family as they did not have time. They then took her to the Ukiah shelter who reached out to GGLRR to see if we could pull her and find her a GREAT home.
 
What Chloe’s foster says: 
Chloe is the best dog. She is a total love who loves belly rubs, cuddles and being around her people. She is fantastic in doors and will settle in any room you are in. She even knows “out” for out of the kitchen and will lay down in our family room while we eat, though she would love to sit under us waiting for a morsel to drop.  She knows sit, stay, shake for commands and sits at the back door when she needs to use the bathroom which is not very often. When we leave for short periods of time she goes in her crate and at night she sleeps in our room on her bed. On walks she pulls a little on the leash but corrects quickly. We are working on heel which she is getting good at. She can walk by other dogs but needs to be heeling next to you. She doesn’t like other dogs in her space and she will let them know but she won’t go after another dog aggressively. She would really like to chase squirrels or cats on walks but as long as you are attentive and she knows you are in control as soon as her ears perk up and you say no and put her in check she leaves it. I don’t feel like she would like the dog park. We go out for a walk about 1.5 to 2 miles and a bit of fetch in the morning and we usually play in our backyard in the afternoon or if we feel like she needs a bit more exercise or to release some energy we go on a short late afternoon walk. 

Chloe is fine around kids but would most likely do better around older kids. She rides great in the car and is a mellow and sweet girl.
 
 
What Chloe’s Rescue Rep says: 
Chloe is a great dog and deserves to find her last home! Chloe needs exercise and a home that will be her leader and not let her lead. She loves people and they said she was very sweet to older people. 

She is housetrained, loves the water, enjoys running and playing fetch. She may dig if left alone in the backyard; most dogs will if they are bored. The previous owners describe her as friendly, playful, loves people and picks up things quickly. She may jump up to greet you and she could use better leash manners. She should not be in a home with another dog and a home with cats. 

Exercise is key for Chloe! The shelter tested her with a variety of dogs, and she did not have any issues and they felt she is a dog that will not go out of her way to create any issues.
 
Medical: 
Chloe has no health issues. She is spayed, up to date on her shots, heartworm negative and is microchipped. I spoke to the previous owners and they did not have any health issues with her.
 
Chloe is currently located in: 
Brentwood
 
If you are interested in adopting Chloe, please contact Rescue Rep Liz at liz@jobshopsf.com

animal.description:
It’s no secret that we are drawn to the overlooked, the shut down, and the medical cases. And this time it’s no different. The sweetest, saddest, most shy girl was surrendered to an area animal control because they had too many animals. Her world was rocked. She would pancake or bolt if there were any quick movements near her, new people made her back away, and no amount of treats would make her change her mind. With time and lots of patience she did warm up to a few staff members. When one of our experienced foster families fell for her preciousness and went to meet her the unbelievable happened...she warmed up to him almost instantly and took treats he was offering! ? She literally picked the people that would help her shine! 
Please help us welcome the newest member of the CTP family...Zelda! 
More info as she settles in.

animal.description:
MEET HAYLEE!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. She is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A3977607.

Haylee has been at the shelter for over 60 days now and it's time for her to go home! She wants to go home too! When volunteers take Haylee for a walk and she sees the parking lot of the shelter, she pulls towards it because she's ready to get in the car. Haylee is a sweet girl that loves her treats and knows how to "sit" and "shake". She pulls on the leash when she first gets out of her kennel to go for a walk but calms down once she gets into her walk. She hasn't reacted to any other dogs in the kennels when she's being taken out or when she sees another dog on the walking trail. She watches and wags her tail and continues her walk.

Haylee was in a home for over a year and she is potty trained. The owner did tell us that she doesn't like children, loud noises like rain and going to the vet. She has to have a dog introduction if a potential adopter already has dogs at home. She cannot go to a home with children or if children visit the home. Haylee is such a great dog! If you think she would be a good fit in your home, please come and meet her today!

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description: Meet our little stud muffin Tucker! He is a neutered 12 year old Shih Tzu with the personality of a 90 lbs Lab! He is only 12 lbs!! He is so full of love and life and wants all the attention.  He loves squeaky toys and dog beds and anything that will entertain him! He was in a loving home most of his life but his previous owners gave him away once they were placed in a nursing home and could not keep him anymore.  Poor Tucker.  He was not surrendered for any fault of his or his previous owners.  They then gave him to a young girl who promise to keep and love him forever but this ended up not happening.  She had Tucker for 6 months and did nothing with him at all.  Then when she had to move she needed to rehome him which is how he ended up with us.  He was severely matted and needed a dental badly.  We were able to get him all cleaned up and groomed, dental done on him, he tested heartworm negative but new adopters will need to keep him on heartworm preventative and retest again in 6 months, and now we are trying to find his forever home.  We definitely want a family that will love him unconditionally until his last day.  If you think you might be the best fit for him, email us at LongJ1003@aol.com and Katybug6067@gmail.com.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Ollie. I am a 6 year old, 13 lbs Terrier/Pomeranian mix. Everyone says I am the cutest little guy with my scruffy face. I am looking for a quiet home where I will be your one and only.  Most of the time, I am fine with other dogs, but I will growl if another dog wants attention from my person. So I will need a home where I can be the center of your love and affection without needing to share. I also need a home without children. Young children can be loud and move quickly and that makes me feel uncomfortable.

I will  need a home in a quiet neighborhood. A fenced in yard would be wonderful as I love to run and play. I am not a city dog and would not do well in an apartment/busy complex/neighborhood.
 I can feel nervous meeting new people, so I will need time and patience when meeting unknown people and when in new situations. I am neutered and up to date on vaccinations and grooming. I walk well on a leash and currently use a 10 ft lead when using the bathroom.

I am not big on traveling. I prefer to stay home except when riding to and from the groomer and/or veterinarian. When traveling on long trips, I get very nervous and will need to be snuggled. Finding  a house sitter or flexibly boarding would be the best option for me when my owner plans a long trip. I do not like to be crated but luckily I do not need to be. I have free roam of the house and do well when I am alone. 

I am fostered in Mechanicsville, MD. If you are looking for a loyal and devoted best friend, please go to puppypawsrescue.org
 and fill out an application for Ollie. I'll be here waiting for you!

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies)  and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

animal.description:
Zion is an 8 month old AKC Siberian Husky pup with lots of love for a forever family.  Those of you who still love the outdoors even in our cold MN winter months, this guy is for you!  He loves being outside, sniffing around in the snow, and playing with other dogs, and getting affection and love from his people.

Zion has tons of potential and is learning a lot in foster care.  Unfortunately he was not trained & always given his way the first 8 months of his life so we are working on reversing some of those bad habits and establishing boundaries.  He is currently working on his recall, leave it, drop, stay, and place among many other things!  Due to his size and the training that needs to continue for him he would likely be best in a home without small children.  

We are looking for a home for Zion that is a strong leader and motivated to continue his training which will create an unbreakable bond with a new dog. 


_______________
Bold Animal Advocates is a holistic animal rescue who utilizes natural alternatives to traditional dog preventatives, medications, and vaccination when available & also feeds an optimal raw food diet. While not required to continue, preference will go to those willing to continue care holistically.

We value training and our dogs being well behaved members of our community so continued training for all of our dogs for the remainder of their lives is required.  

We have recommendations on our website  for companies that we love and trust if you would like suggestions.
boldanimaladvocates.com

***Please apply here***
https://forms.gle/g5EKPNw8steM2roo7

We will review applications for and reach out to those who we think may be a perfect fit to discuss next steps.  Please note that during this time we may be unable to respond to email & phone inquiries so the best way to reach us will be by applying.  We are required to charge sales tax on this adoption fee of 7.125% and accept cash, check, or Paypal at the time of adoption.  Thank you!

animal.description:
"You Ain't Nuthin' But a Hound Dog." WRONG! Sheldon is so much more than a hound dog! He's an amazing guard dog when he doesn't know someone. Never any worry of home intrusion with this big guy's bark. And yet he's as gentle as a lamb with barky 10 lb chihuahuas that want to boss him around. Sheldon loves 'his people' and would love to have a forever home of his very own! Complete an application to meet Sheldon -- we'll bring him to your home for a visit.

Dogs in our foster care program are:

spayed/neutered

microchipped

up to date on all vaccinations

negative for heartworms and on regular heartworm preventative OR recently treated for heartworms and on regular heartworm preventative (It can take up to 6 months for a dog to test negative for heartworm after treatments. We will provide you all the medical documentation regarding the pet's treatment.)

NOT IN A SHELTER FACILITY. They are in loving foster care homes where they have received training and socialization to help them fit into your home more quickly. Therefore we schedule appointments in advance and do not have a general facility where you can view multiple dogs at one time.

Note about Breeds:

We do NOT do DNA tests on the dogs in our program. Many are found as puppies or young adults and we do not have any information about their parents. We select dog breed mixes based on recommendation from shelter staff and/or veterinarians and our experience in working with thousands of dogs. We consider the physical and behavioral traits of the dog as well as their size. If you are looking for a purebred dog and want to argue with us about breed standards, we encourage you to work with breed specific rescue organizations. If you are looking for a dog who have great personalities despite a mixed background (like most of us humans!), we'd love to work with you!

There are a few steps to set up the adoption.

Complete the
Adoption Application
online. Many dogs receive multiple applications and we review applications in the order they are received.

Foster will review your application and reach out to you to schedule a "virtual meet and greet".

Participate in a "virtual meet and greet".
This is a great way for you to get to see the dog in a setting where it is already comfortable and get lots of questions answered to determine if the dog's personality and energy level are a good fit.
This is also a great time to have a virtual "home visit" to show the fence, home, etc to minimize the amount of time the foster would need to come into your home later.

The foster and adoption coordinator will review the applications and notes from the virtual meet and greets and set up in person home visits with the applicants we feel are the best match for the dog's personality and energy level.

Trial Adoption -dogs are eligible for a trial adoption with the adopter that we feel is the best match. Trial adoptions last up to 3 nights and the foster will provide 3 days worth of food, information about the dog's schedule, and other tips and tricks to make it a successful transition. The adopt fee can be paid online as a deposit to start the trial adoption. If the dog is not the right fit, we refund the adoption fee.

As a 100% volunteer-powered organization, we appreciate your patience as we review the applications.

Itzy, 3 month old female Catahoula Mix.

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website- www.luckymuttsrescue.org and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.  We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions.  Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.   Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 

Current Adoption Fees Are:
$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary

The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen, we receive several applications for each dog. Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.   Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will be in active status for a period of six months.  We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  Should you see a dog that interests you, please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!

Vito is roughly 5 years young, and weighs 63 pounds. He is a strong dog, but is learning to walk politely on leash and exhibit manners with people. Overall he is a big mush! Vito will be undergoing ear surgery on Feb 12th; afterwards he will have limited hearing but he’ll feel so much better! Recovery care is minimal and he should be fully recovered 2-3 weeks post-surgery. 
For dogs undergoing medical treatments, we offer foster-to-adopt to families interested in a dog. Vito will receive the surgery at Gigi’s by one of our veterinarians and the cost is covered by Gigi's. If you are interested in Vito, please email us at adopt@gigis.org

Dogs from Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:

animal.description:
Let us show you Scotch - a sweet and curious guy who loves treats, going for walks, car rides, and chasing frisbees! 

Scotch was transferred to us from another shelter, and they stated that he was always excited and super friendly when meeting new people! He loves attention, belly rubs, and snuggling! He even is a great co-pilot in the car, and has good manners when in a home. He does pull on his leash when excited, it's only because he wants to do his own thing and explore the world as much as possible! He would benefit from a harness while walking, and some additional leash training in his new home! 

His previous shelter stated that he loves female dogs and is selective with male dogs, so Scotch would like to meet any potential adopters and their canine companions before heading home! Scotch seems to have high prey drive and is a bit too interested in cats/small animals - he will need a home without small pets. Scotch has also seemed uncomfortable around children he has met at the shelter, and would prefer to meet any new family members to ensure he will be compatible for the home. 

Scotch has been treated for heartworm disease. THS requires all adopters of heartworm positive dogs to purchase a 1 year supply of heartworm preventative at the time of adoption.

Please follow this link to learn more about our current adoption process: https://toledohumane.org/covid-19-update

animal.description:
Meet Louis Vitton! 

How on earth is this sweet beautiful puppy still available? Louis vitton has been in Wisconsin for 3 weeks and has had very little interest for furever homes. He just can’t understand why. Yes he is a black pup and yes he is probably part pit-but those aren’t his fault. He is sweet and spunky and has endless love and kisses to give! He is mostly potty trained. He does great in a crate while his humans are gone for work and keeps his cage dry. His favorite place to sleep is in bed with humans-but how can you tell that sweet little face no?! Louie hasn’t met a soul he doesn’t love-cats, dogs, big and little humans. He really is the whole package! If interested in adopting this sweet boy apply through mapawsmepetrescue.com.

Interested in meeting Louis Vitton? 

All Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue dogs are in homes with foster families; we do not have a shelter where dogs are available for daily viewing.

Our process is as follows:
1.  Review our policies and adoption radius  on our website: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/
2.  Submit an application for review and approval;
3.  MPM Rescue reviews application and checks vet records and references;
4.  MPM foster contacts approved applicant(s) to arrange a home check and meeting with available dog(s);
5.   If there is a good fit, adoption is completed with a contract and fees (payable via check or cash).

The adoption fee is listed here: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/

Dogs from Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
- Spay/Neuter surgery
- Age appropriate vaccinations
- Heartworm test (for dogs over 6mo) and treatment if positive
- Microchip
- Deworming
- Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
- Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

*Please note that the identified breed(s) are best guesses. We very rarely have information on our dogs' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays.*

animal.description: Welp! Howdy!  My name is Titus! Boy do I have a story to tell!  I don’t know exactly how it happened, but I was injured and a Good Samaritan picked me up by the road!  I guess I had been hit by a car. Anyway my new friend took me to the vet! They fixed me up by repairing my hip! Yep I am good as new!  They tried to find me a new home, but didn’t have any luck. They knew at the shelter lots more people would be able to see me and I would have a much better chance of getting adopted. So here I am! Ready to find a new family and have a fresh start in life!  I have all of my vaccinations, I am heartworm negative, I have a microchip, and I have been neutered. I would like to thank my kind rescuer who picked me up from the side of the road and took me to the vet. Thanks to the doctors at Carriage Hills who made my hip “all better!” I am a one-year-old terrier mix. Now all I need is a new family to love for the rest of my life!

animal.description:
Maizy is a four year old female bloodhound. This tan, droopy-eared girl weighs around 85 lbs. Maizy was used as a breeder before being abandoned last year. She has been in a foster home learning what it means to be a member of a family. Maizy’s fosters have multiple other large dogs and she has also been around a small dog. She has done well with kids during meet and greets too. Maizy would love to find an owner committed to keeping her healthy and happy. Her fosters say “she loves to run in the yard and then come inside to be a couch potato.” To adopt Maizy, complete an application at ITVrescue.org.

All of our animals are examined by a veterinarian, given age-appropriate vaccinations, dewormed, microchipped, spayed or neutered, heartworm tested and treated if necessary.

Please realize that many of our animals are kept in foster homes. Please complete an adoption application at http://itvrescue.org/adoption-application/ in order to meet with one of our animals. There is no obligation in completing the application, but it helps us find an animal that is most appropriate for your family.  The ITV Rescue Center is open Tuesdays 12-5; Wednesdays 12-7; Thursdays 12-5; Fridays 12-5 and Saturdays 10-5.  The Rescue Center is located at 1417 N. Stockwell Road.  You are welcome to come to our rescue center during open hours to see all of our great adoptable animals. Thank you for your interest in our animals!

NOTE: Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable, so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

Please go to www.mobilespca.org and complete an online application. Someone from the office will give you a call and set up an appointment for you to come meet me. ADOPTION FEE: $150 10 Years Old 23 Pounds Heart Worm Positive -On Treatment ABOUT OUR PETS: All of our pets available for adoption have been spayed/neutered, tested for heartworms, given age-appropriate vaccinations, microchipped and are on flea and heartworm preventative medication. ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS: To give each dog the best possible home we require a completed Adoption Application. Screening and approval by our Adoption Coordinators and a home visit may be required to make sure this pet fits into your home and the home fits our pet. CONTACT US:If you would like to give this dog a good home please call the Mobile SPCA office at 251-633-3531 or drop by our Adoption Center located at 620 Zeigler Circle W, Mobile, AL 36608 - Tuesday through Friday from 9 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. and Thursday and Saturday from 9 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. CAN'T ADOPT? SPONSOR OR DONATE! This wonderful animal is just one of many in our care right now. Your sponsorship helps us provide shelter, food, and tender loving care for the animals until they find new loving homes. Adoption fees do not cover our expenses, so your sponsorship will make a positive impact on our organization and especially on our animals’ well being. Please note: we are not a chapter or affiliate of any national animal organization. We are, moreover, very grateful for your generosity. Thank you!

animal.description: Nala is a lovely 9-month-old mixed-breed girl who currently weighs about 45 pounds. She came to SFAS when her guardian could no longer care for her.
